The Brooklyn Nets will wear their nickname player jerseys Jan. 10 against the Miami Heat at Barclays Center. Fans can buy the nickname jerseys starting Wednesday at the team store at Barclays Center. Nets jerseys featuring nicknames like "D-Will" (Deron Williams), "Truth" (Paul Pierce) and "JJ" (Joe Johnson) cost $110 (swingman), $70 (replica) or $50 (kids). Fans can also buy nickname T-shirts as well. The Nets will offer fans nickname food and beverage selections at their concessions stands, and each one of their chef tables at the 40/40 Club & Restaurant will be named after a different player's nickname.